Condition : 8 - Notwithstanding the details shown on the approved plans and set out in the supporting information, Landscape and Ecological Enhancement and Management Plans shall be submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority prior to the commencement of any above ground works. The Plan shall include details of all measures to provide biodiversity gain onsite and offsite, including but not limited to: 
-	Details of native and wildlife friendly planting, including mixed native species hedging, low flowering amenity grass and night scented species. The species list should indicate which species are native and which have known value for local wildlife;
-	Details of all biodiverse roofs (including any Biosolar roofs) including details of extensive substrate base, features to be included within the substrate e.g. rope coils, sand, gravel, etc., and details of any seeding/plug plant choice (in accordance with The Gro Green Roof Code 2021);
-	Orientation, target species and location for at least 6x integrated swift bricks/boxes and at least 4x bat boxes and 4x bee bricks to be integrated with the new buildings;
-	Details of deadwood habitat and other habitats for invertebrates;
-	A bat sensitive post-construction lighting plan, including lux spill diagrams, to ensure that any lighting will be of a specification that minimises its impacts on bats, onsite and adjacent habitats in accordance with the BCT and ILP 2023 Guidance Note (including having a colour temperature of <2700k, no uplighters, no upwards light spill and no light spill onto the adjacent habitats);
-	Details on the management to be implemented post-construction shall also be submitted, which shall include management responsibilities and maintenance schedules for all hard and soft landscaped areas as well as the above-mentioned measures to provide biodiversity gain.

The approved details shall be implemented prior to first occupation of the development and maintained thereafter.

